About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great piece of luggage, much roomier than you would expect at a great price!
reviews.reviewText: An amazing piece of luggage for an amazing price! I purchased the black, as it was the lowest priced of the 20 inch model. It is a sleek looking piece much more like an expensive piece of luggage. I've already used it on a trip to Boston, so I can say without a doubt that it handles beautifully! The handles allow you to easily put it in and out of the trunk of the car, and the wheels maneuver easily in all directions and over all terrains: bumpy concrete, smooth tile and carpet. By accident I dropped the luggage while loading it (my fault completely) and it escaped unharmed. The body has a very fine texture print so small dings don't seem to appear.The joke at my house is that this small piece of luggage is like a clown car! When I was sharing how much I packed, people couldn't believe how much I kept pulling out of the bag. Typically I need to sit on my luggage to even begin to get near to closing it, but I found that I had room to spare with this piece. It seems to me that the construction is so deep and rectangular that no room is sacrificed for trying to create a slimmer profile. As I've already pointed out, however, this is so well made that in my opinion it is much nicer looking that other models I've had, and it certainly holds a good deal more due to the depth of each side of the luggage.The handle extends easily and retracts easily as well. The zippers work smoothly with the luggage opening complete for easy packing. The interior is separated by a zippered separator, ensuring that your clothes remain in place while traveling and upon opening the luggage. There is a small zippered interior pouch, which I didn't use but you may want to use for small items.In summary, I couldn't be happier. The price point, the looks and the overall ease of use of this piece of luggage made it a great find for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good product, good price
reviews.reviewText: My wife and I bought this as a carry-on piece of luggage for our flight to Mexico. It performed well. And, it fit into the new overhead bins they have for carry-ons. The only thing I don't know is how well it will hold up in the long run. Newer bags such as then appear to be hard-sided, but in reality they have a (seemingly) flimsy outer shell. Most bags nowadays seem to be this way. But, I was impressed at how smoothly it rolled on both hard floors and on thinner carpet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice bright color, durable and rolls well
reviews.reviewText: Bought for a carry on that handles easy, nice telescoping handle and adequate space. Perfect for short trips and if you decide to check it, it is distinguishable on a luggage carousel. The handle will accommodate back pack straps to lighten your shoulder load if needed. Comes with locks as well if you decide to check it to discourage people from peeking. Nice zippered and separated sections to keep things organized and place dirty clothes and shoes in for the trip home.

La valigia è un ottimo prodotto,maneggevole grazie alle 4 ruote , leggero e bello da vedere (io ho preso la colorazione blu).E' anche espandibile grazie ad una doppia cerniera che ne copre il perimetro.Gli spazi all'interno sono quelli tipici di una valigia da usarsi come bagaglio a mano.Due pecche che non mi fanno dare le 5 stelle sono la mancanza della chiusura Tsa (ma si può risolvere con un lucchetto) e la lunghezza dell'asta della maniglia che per una persona piuttosto alta come me (188cm) risulta piuttosto corta.Per il resto ottimo acquisto che mi sento di consigliare.
